# Code Style

## Functions

- Single responsibility; prefer early return / guard clauses
- Target ≤ 50 lines per function; split larger service methods
- Pure helpers in `shared/utils/`
- Avoid deep nesting (>3 levels)

## Naming

- Descriptive names: `verifyAccessToken`, not `verify`
- No magic numbers — use constants or env
- Match existing module naming: `auth.service.ts`, `auth.controller.ts`

## Imports order

1. Node built-ins
2. External packages
3. Internal aliases / shared
4. Relative imports

Alphabetical within each group. Match surrounding file style.

## Comments

- No obvious comments (`// get user`)
- Comment only: complex business rules, workarounds, non-obvious algorithms

## Duplication

- Extract repeated Zod fields to shared schemas
- Extract repeated Prisma `select` shapes to constants

## Formatting

- Match existing file indentation and quote style
- Run TypeScript compiler before claiming done

## Avoid

- Large god classes/files
- Duplicate error handling outside middleware
- Copy-paste across modules — extract to shared when third use appears
